<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="483" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/8–1147: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-11">August 11,
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received August 11—3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2624. All Soviet papers August 9 carried text of communiqué by Mongolian
                        People’s Republic denying Mongolian and asserting Chinese responsibility for
                        border incidents in Sinkiang.</p>
                    <p>Department pass Nanking.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>